# Documentation Index

This directory contains comprehensive documentation for the LangChain RAG project.
Start with `01_system_architecture.md` if you are new to the project.

| File | What it covers |
|---|---|
| `01_system_architecture.md` | High-level system design, component diagram, data flow, and the two main phases (ingestion vs query) |
| `02_config_explained.md` | Every parameter in `config.py` explained line by line, including how they interact |
| `03_ingest_explained.md` | Every function in `ingest.py` explained line by line, with a full ingestion flow diagram |
| `04_app_explained.md` | Every function and section in `app.py` explained line by line, including Streamlit's re-run model |
| `05_operational_mechanics.md` | End-to-end walkthrough of every user action: startup, upload, select, question, follow-up, delete, restart |

## Recommended reading order for newcomers

1. `01_system_architecture.md` — understand the big picture before any code
2. `02_config_explained.md` — understand all tunable parameters
3. `03_ingest_explained.md` — understand how PDFs become a searchable index
4. `04_app_explained.md` — understand the UI and RAG chain construction
5. `05_operational_mechanics.md` — see everything working together end-to-end
